WorldVeg seeks a Laboratory Assistant (Project-based) at its Headquarters in Shanhua, Tainan, Taiwan, to work in the Vegetable Biodiversity Cluster of the Flagship Safe & Sustainable Value Chains.  The position is for a period of one year.  Renewal of the position depends on the performance of the incumbent and of availability of funding.  This is a nationally recruited position and open for Taiwan nationals only. 

Job Responsibilities

•	Detect viruses by molecular diagnostic methods and conduct molecular characterization of viruses, which involves molecular biology techniques such as nucleic acid extraction, PCR, RT-PCR, gel electrophoresis, viral gene cloning, plasmid extraction, restriction enzyme digestion, primer design, and sequence analysis;
•	Screen vegetable accessions/breeding lines for resistance to viruses, including preparation of virus inoculum, inoculation of plants with virus, symptom observation and recording, and confirmation of virus presence in the plants using molecular diagnostic methods;  
•	Assist in compiling and summarizing the research results, preparation of project reports, and performing administrative activities related to the project; 
•	Others: take care of daily works in the laboratory and as assigned by scientist, such as cleaning laboratory, preparing buffer/medium/chemical, conducting collection of virus isolates and virus disease surveys, collecting/sorting plant disease samples, assisting in training of trainees and students in virology, etc. 


Qualifications

•	Have a B.S. degree in Plant Pathology, Biology, Biotechnology, Agriculture or a related field, ideally with some experience of molecular biology techniques in plant virology; 
•	Be interested to learn and broaden skills and gain competence in this field; 
•	Have good organizing and coordination skills; 
•	Have a reasonable command of English (written and spoken); 
•	Have experience of using computers for preparing documents, reports, data analysis and communication.

The Reward: This is a Nationally Recruited Staff (NRS) position with competitive pay and benefits. The initial appointment is for one year and may be extended depending on requirements, funding availability, and performance of the incumbent.


病毒組  徵 「計畫實驗室助理」乙名

主要負責工作內容：
•	協助並負責病毒的檢測與鑑定，包括萃取核酸，進行PCR、RT-PCR、膠體電泳，病毒基因選殖，質體DNA萃取，限制酶切割反應，引子設計及序列分析。
•	協助並負責蔬菜作物的抗病篩選：準備病毒接種源，人工接種，病毒檢測與鑑定，病徵觀察與記錄。
•	協助實驗結果彙整與計畫報告撰寫，並協助計畫相關之行政工作。
•	執行實驗室及溫、網室的例行性工作，包括配製藥品，實驗室清潔，參與病毒株的收集與田野病害調查，收集並分類病害樣品，協助訓練學員及學生等。

應徵資格：	
取得植物病理、生物、生物技術、農業或相關領域的學士學位；
具備英文溝通能力與植物病毒學相關之分子遺傳技術的應徵者，將優先考慮。




應徵方式：	請將英文應徵信、履歷表(含照片)以及三位推薦人姓名、聯絡方式 (包括電話、電子郵件信箱) 寄到：亞蔬 – 世界蔬菜中心, 台南市善化區郵政信箱42號 , 人力資源室 或 電子郵件信箱: jobapply@worldveg.org.生醫工程學類,生命科學學門,農林漁牧學門

